// Code-signing settings for the MyPortrait Xcode target.
//
// **Defaults below are for fresh contributors.** They use Xcode's automatic
// signing with the upstream maintainer's Apple Developer team — which works
// out of the box only for the maintainer; everyone else has to override.
//
// To override (gitignored, per-machine):
//   Create `Support/Signing.local.xcconfig` with whichever of these settings
//   you need:
//
//   Contributor (you have your own Apple ID, want stable TCC permissions):
//       DEVELOPMENT_TEAM = YOURTEAMID
//
//   Maintainer (use the local self-signed cert that the release pipeline uses,
//   so Xcode debug builds and release dmg share the same TCC entries):
//       CODE_SIGN_STYLE   = Manual
//       CODE_SIGN_IDENTITY = MyPortraitDev
//       DEVELOPMENT_TEAM  =
//
// Then re-run `xcodegen generate`. The `#include?` below is "optional include"
// (Xcode 11+ syntax) — missing file is fine, present file wins.
//
// Why these settings have to live in an xcconfig and not in project.yml's
// `settings.base`: settings.base entries are emitted as per-target build
// settings in the .pbxproj, which **override xcconfig values**. Putting the
// defaults here is what lets Signing.local.xcconfig actually win.

CODE_SIGN_STYLE  = Automatic
DEVELOPMENT_TEAM = VYHNX2Y2AL

#include? "Signing.local.xcconfig"
